{{Quote|Corellian Security informs us there is no such vessel as ''Shadow Bird''. However, the ''Millennium Falcon'' is cleared for immediate departure.|[[Corellian Control]], to [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Recovery">''[[The New Jedi Order: Recovery]]''</ref>}}
'''''Shadow Bird''''' was an alias that the [[Freighter/Legends|freighters]] [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] and ''[[Sureshot]]'' flew under in the months following the [[Battle of Duro (Yuuzhan Vong War)|Battle of Duro]] during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]].

==History==
When he landed the ''Millennium Falcon'' on [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] in order to ensure that his wife, [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]], received treatment for injuries inflicted during the First Battle of Duro, Han Solo identified the ''Falcon'' as ''Shadow Bird'' to [[Corellian Control]] so that their arrival would not attract unwanted attention. After they were forced to leave Corellia by [[Thrackan Sal-Solo]], Han attempted to remain discreet by using the alias when requesting clearance to depart. However, Corellian Control had been informed by [[Corellian Security Force]] that the ''Shadow Bird'' was in fact the ''Millennium Falcon'' and broadcast the freighter's true name over an open channel, alerting several [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] to the ''Falcon''{{'s}} location.

Later, when Han and Leia traveled to [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] in order to undermine support for the [[Peace Vote]] by accusing [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Viqi Shesh]], its chief proponent, of corruption and to find a [[nervesplicer]] to help Leia heal her injuries, they arranged for [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Izal Waz]]'s [[YT-1300 light freighter/Legends|YT-1300 light freighter]] ''[[Sureshot]]'' to be cosmetically altered to look like the ''Millennium Falcon'' and equipped it with a [[slave circuit]] to allow Waz to remotely pilot the ''Sureshot'' from the freighter ''[[Jolly Man]]'' on their approach to Coruscant. In order to further sell the illusion that the ''Sureshot'' was the ''Falcon'', it flew under the alias ''Shadow Bird''. This gambit resulted in the destruction of the ''Sureshot'', but allowed Han and Leia to fulfill their goals, albeit not without some difficulty.

